<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-73-1038 </DOCNO><TEXT>The characteristics of the hydrodynamic structure of a thin liquid layerwith a gas bubble are examined for different heat and mass transfer mechanisms.The formation of one (Pe greater than 1) and two (Pe less than 1) vortexflows near the gas bubble is demonstrated. It is found that the pairinteraction of gas bubbles is realized through the interaction of large-scaleliquid perturbations, such as vortex flows. 8 references.</TEXT></DOC>